<HEADLINE> HK Official on Arrangement of Legislature Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Secretary for
Constitutional Affairs Robin Ip Thursday revealed the specific
arrangement of the government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) for the May Legislative Council
elections.
</P>
<P>
The 60 members of the first Legislative Council of the Hong
Kong SAR will be made up of 20 to be returned from the
geographical constituencies through direct election, 30 by
functional constituencies and 10 by an 800-strong Election
Committee.
</P>
<P>
According to IP, Hong Kong will be divided into five
geographical constituencies -- Hong Kong Island, Kowloon East,
Kowloon West, "New Territories" East and "New Territories" West
each with 3 to 5 seats in proportion to the number of residents.
</P>
<P>
The list voting system will be adopted during the geographical
constituencies election, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ip explained that the list voting system is a form of
proportional representation voting system, which is open, widely
accepted as fair and is used in many countries and will more
accurately reflect voter preference in the election results.
</P>
<P>
There are a total of 28 functional constituencies, he said,
with 27 functional constituencies producing one seat each and the
labor functional constituency producing three seats.
</P>
<P>
The 800 members of the Election Committee will come equally
from four sectors: industry, commerce and finance; the
professionals; labor, social services and religious; and members
of the Provisional legislative Council, Hong Kong deputies to the
National People's Congress, representatives of Hong Kong members
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference and representatives of district-based
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The election of the Election Committee members will be held on
April 2, and then they will elect 10 to the Legislative Council on
 May 24.
</P>
<P>
Ip said that the objective of the above arrangement is "to
produce a credible and representative legislature".
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the candidates for Election Committee
subsector elections will be nominated from March 13 to 20 while
the candidates for the Legislative Council election will be
nominated from April 9 to 24.  
</P>
</TEXT>
