<HEADLINE> Nepal's Ruling Partners Decide to Defeat Censure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Ruling partners of Nepali
Prime Minister Surya Bahadur Thapa Thursday decided to defeat the
no-confidence motion tabled against him, Radio Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary party of the Nepali Congress (NC) unanimously
passed a resolution from the party's Central Working Committee
calling for unitedly defeating the censure motion moved on
February 6 by the main opposition Communist Party of Nepal (United
Marxism-Leninism, CPN-UML) and a breakaway faction of the ruling
National Democratic Party (RPP).
</P>
<P>
The RPP led by Prime Minister Thapa and the Nepal Sadbhavana
Party (NSP) both have issued whips demanding their MPs to vote
against the motion.
</P>
<P>
The CPN-UML earlier issued a whip directing all its 89 MPs to
vote for the censure motion.
</P>
<P>
As set by Speaker Ram Chandra Poudyal, the Lower House will
discuss the motion next Tuesday and vote on it Friday.
</P>
<P>
A simple majority of 103 votes is required to pass the motion
in the 205-seat Lower House.
</P>
<P>
It is still hard to predict the outcome. But as days go by,
horse trading is gaining momentum.
</P>
<P>
The present coalition government comprising the NC, the RPP and
the NSP came to power last October. There have been three
coalition governments in Nepal since 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
