<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Starts Luxembourg Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived Thursday afternoon in Luxembourg, the first leg of his
week-long three-nation European tour.
</P>
<P>
Li was on a two-day official good-will visit at the invitation
of Luxembourg Prime Minister Jean-Claude Juncker, who gave the
Chinese guest a red-carpet welcome at the airport.
</P>
<P>
In his host's company, the Chinese premier reviewed the guards
of honor of Luxembourg armed forces.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech upon arrival -- the first time by a Chinese
premier since the two countries forged diplomatic ties in 1972, Li
said he was "very pleased" to visit this West European country.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the efforts of both sides, he said, the
China-Luxembourg relationship has expanded rapidly in recent years
with frequent personnel exchanges and fruitful cooperation in the
fields of economy, trade, science, technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government attaches importance to its relations
with Luxembourg and stands ready to continue its effort in
developing the friendly cooperation in various fields with your
country on the basis of the principles of mutual respect, equality
and mutual benefit," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that this visit will further enhance the mutual
understanding between our two peoples and promote the smooth
growth of the friendly relations between our two countries," he
said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Luxembourg, Li is scheduled to "have
extensive exchange of views with leaders of Luxembourg on
bilateral relations and other international issues of common
interest and meet personages from all circles."
</P>
<P>
Li's entourage include his wife Zhu Lin, Director of the
Foreign Affairs Office of the State Council Liu Huaqiu, Governor
of Guangdong Province Lu Ruihua, Chinese ambassador to Luxembourg
Shi Yanhua, Vice-Foreign Minister Wang Yingfan, Vice-Minister in
charge of the State Planning Commission Chen Tonghai,
Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi
Guangsheng, President of the China National Offshore Oil
Corp. Wang Yan, Deputy Director of the Foreign Affairs Office of
the State Council Lu Congmin, Vice-Minister of the Civil Aviation
Administration of China Wang Li'an and Special Assistant Wan
Jinchang.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that Li will meet Prince Henri and confer with
Juncker on promoting the bilateral relations and on other issues
of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
After the Luxembourg tour, Li will proceed to the Netherlands
for a four-day official good-will visit at the invitation of his
Dutch counterpart Wim Kok. 
</P>
</TEXT>
