<HEADLINE> Sudanese First Vice President Killed in Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese First Vice President
El-Zubeir Mohammed Salih was killed Thursday in a plane crash in
southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the presidency said that Salih was killed
when his plane plunged into the Sobat River in al-Nasir, about 800
kilometers south of the capital Khartoum, due to the poor
visibility caused by bad weather.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that also on board the plane was an
entourage, including Minister of Culture and Information Tabib
Ibrahim Mohammed Khair, accompanying Salih.
</P>
<P>
But it did not mention who of the entourage were among those
killed.
</P>
<P>
Salih, a key member of the Muslim government, was on a two-day
visit to Malakal, capital of Upper Nile State, in southern Sudan.
</P>
</TEXT>
