<HEADLINE> Albania's Ramiz Alia to Undergo Heart Surgery in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Former Albanian President Ramiz
Alia will on Friday arrive in the northern Greek city of
Thessaloniki to undergo heart surgery.
</P>
<P>
The 73-year-old Albanian leader, who was given a medical visa
by the Greek consulate in Tirana, will be operated on at the
George Papanicolaou hospital on Saturday or Sunday by Greek heart
surgeon Panayotis Spyrou, the semi-official Athens News Agency
(ANA) reported
</P>
<P>
Alia, who has had severe heart problems for the past five
years, became Albanian president in 1985 after the death of Enver
Hoxha. 
</P>
