<HEADLINE> Lesotho Ratifies Treaty of African Economic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho has ratified the
treaty of African Economic Community (AEC), according to a press
release issued by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) today.
</P>
<P>
The release said, Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim at
Africa Unity House on Wednesday received new ambassador of
Lesotho to Ethiopia Masuhla Leteka who deposited the African
Economic Community instrument of ratification on behalf of his
country, thereby making Lesotho the 42nd OAU member state to do
so.
</P>
<P>
It said that Salim expressed thanks and appreciation to the
envoy, adding that the depositing demonstrated Lesotho's
commitment to the AEC treaty and an understanding of its
importance since coming into force in 1994.
</P>
<P>
It said that Salim noted that the treaty is capable of meeting
many international challenges to Africa including the prevailing
wave of globalization, and in this connection he appealed to
member states of the OAU who have not done so to move forward and
ratify the treaty.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Leteka commended the existence of the AEC, which he
described as " a cornerstone in Africa's efforts to achieve
economic cooperation and integration" so as to enable it
participate fully in world affairs, the release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
