<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce And Bilkent Announce Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 12 (Xinhua) - Rolls-Royce and Bilkent Holding
of Turkey have formed a joint venture to build an RB211-powered
36MW cogeneration facility at Bilkent University in Ankara,
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The new facility, which will expand an existing 4MW Bilenerji
power facility, will provide efficient electricity and process
steam/hot water to the university and other Bilkent manufacturing
plants, Rolls-Royce announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The facility, which is scheduled to start operation in late
1999, represents an investment of approximately 35 million US
dollars by Rolls-Royce Power Ventures and Bilkent Holding.
</P>
<P>
Under the turnkey construction contract with Foster Wheeler
Bimas, Rolls-Royce said it will supply an RB211 industrial gas
turbine, one of the most reliable and efficient gas turbines
available in this size range, as the main power driver for the
facility.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce Power Ventures and Bilkent are planning to develop
additional cogeneration and industrial power generating facilities
in the 10 to 100MW size range in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Bill Kelly, Managing Director of Rolls-Royce Power Ventures,
said: "We expect the relationship with Bilkent Holding will lead
to many other projects to meet the rapidly expanding industrial
cogeneration market in Turkey."
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce is one of the world's leading power systems
companies, operating in aerospace and industrial power markets.
</P>
</TEXT>
