<HEADLINE> NATO Documentation Center Set Up in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A NATO Documentation Center on
Problems of European security was opened here on Tuesday at the
Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences (INION)
under the Russian Academy of Sciences, according to the Itar-Tass
news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Center was opened in accordance with the Russia-NATO
Founding Act signed on May 27, 1997, in Paris by President Boris
Yeltsin and heads of 17 NATO member states, the Russian Foreign
Ministry was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Center will inform the Russian public of changes in
relations between Russia and NATO and of the role played by the
North Atlantic Alliance in the formation of a new European
security structure, will organize seminars, round-tables and
conferences, as well as accumulate periodicals, documents and
other materials concerning European security issues.
</P>
<P>
It will also activity contribute to the development of
relations between Russia and NATO for the strengthening of
European stability and security, the ministry said.
</P>
