<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
retreated from recent gains and ended sharply lower Thursday,
undermined by a weak Wall Street and market consolidation.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 index of leading shares suffered from bouts
of profit-taking on top of similar activity in New York and closed
down 55.4 points or almost 1 percent at 5,552.5.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's Bank of England inflation report also clouded
market sentiment on fears that interest rates could rise again.
The bank also predicted a sharp fall in UK economic growth.
</P>
