<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese organization
Thursday condemned Israel's illegal detention of Lebanese and
maltreatment of them, calling for international intervention for
the release of the detainees.
</P>
<P>
At an annual conference, Mohammed Soffen, Secretary General of
Lebanon's National Association for Lebanese Detainees in Israeli
Prisons, said that a total of 210 Lebanese are being held in
Israeli prisons inside or outside its territory, of whom 160 are
in south Lebanon's AJ-Khiam Detention Center.
</P>
<P>
He said that about 90 of the detainees are still held without
any trial. Some 40 detainees have died under torture and many
suffer from serious diseases.
</P>
