<HEADLINE> Sudanese First Vice President Killed in Plane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese First Vice President
El-Zubeir Mohammed Salih was killed Thursday in a plane crash in
southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Salih was killed when his plane was making an emergency landing
at al-Nasir Airport due to fierce wind, Sudanese Minister of State
Mohammed Othman Yassin said. He died at the age of 57.
</P>
<P>
The plane slid into the Sobat River because the runway of the
airport, about 800 kilometers south of the capital Khartoum, is
not long enough, Yassin added.
</P>
<P>
The official said that also on board the plane was an entourage
of 52 people accompanying Salih, nine of whom, including Minister
of Culture and Information Tabib Ibrahim Mohammed Khair and
Minister of Animal Resources Musa al-Mak Kur, survived the crash.
</P>
<P>
Salih was on his way back to Khartoum from a two-day trip to
Malakal, capital of Upper Nile State, in southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Sudanese President Omar Hassan Ahmed al-Bashir and Speaker of
the National Assembly Hassan Abdulla al-Turabi addressed the
people who gathered in front of the presidential palace Thursday
afternoon and paid tribute to Salih.
</P>
<P>
Salih, a key member of the Muslim government and a close friend
of al-Turabi, played an important role in the 1989 coup in which
al-Bashir took the power. He had been the first vice president
since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
