over the next two years. The centers will be equipped with
satellite receivers, video recorders, television sets and related
texts, according to Lam.
</P>
<P>
Since its inception, the program has won widespread support
from large enterprises and celebrities in Hong Kong, with the
China Development Services Fund raising 1.4 million Hong Kong
dollars for related efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong fund, a charitable organization, was established
in July 1995. The main purpose of the fund is to seek resources
from both at home and abroad to promote the comprehensive progress
of educational pursuits in China, especially the development of
backward and poverty-stricken areas. 
