opens the way for a definitive Supreme Court ruling on Congress's
historic move in 1996 to give the president more control over
spending. The line-item veto allow's a president to strike
individual items in spending and tax legislation, rather than
force him to choose between signing or rejecting an entire bill
that contains objectionable provisions.
</P>
