<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets United Front Conference Participants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Front has always
been an important magic weapon the Communist Party of China (CPC)
has called on to use to unite the masses in the development of
revolutionary causes and overcoming difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and state president, made the remarks in meeting with
participants attending today's session of a national conference of
the CPC Central Committee United Front Department.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central
Committee Politburo and chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, attended
today's session along with Hu Jintao, member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Central Committee Politburo and member of the
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that China's situation is generally good and the
development of the country's national economy and social sectors
offer many favorable conditions and opportunities.
</P>
<P>
However, he called for full awareness of the growing fierce
competition in the international economy, the financial crisis in
various Southeast Asian and East Asian nations, and the problems
and difficulties the country is encountering in ongoing
development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on the Party members, especially leading Party
officials, to gain a comprehensive clear understanding of the
situation. He also called for maintaining confidence and
redoubling efforts to strengthen the united front to intelligently
promote the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics in
accordance with the dictates of the 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
Members of the nation's United Front have witnessed numerous
monumental achievements in both State and Party affairs over the
past year, including the smooth transfer of Hong Kong to the
motherland, studying and implementing the guidelines of the 15th
CPC National Congress, and helping non-communist parties to elect
new leadership, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee and director of
the United Front Department of the CPC Central Committee, and
leading officials of the departments concerned also attended
today's meeting. 
</P>
