<HEADLINE> Quake Rocks Bandar Lampung, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people in Bandar
Lampung, capital of Indonesia's Lampung province, rushed out of
their homes in panic before midnight Thursday as a strong quake
jolted the city for a few seconds, Antara News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some residents in Way Halim and Karunia Indah housing compounds
in the city said shortly after the quake that they dare not go
back inside their houses as yet for fear of aftershocks, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was quite strong and produced a horrible rumbling
sound, they said.
</P>
<P>
The office of the Meteorological and Geophysical Agency in
Bandar Lampung has yet to determine the intensity of the quake,
which occurred at 10:49 p.m. local time, the report added.
</P>
