believed that Vietnam's joining in the APC would further promote
its relations with Japan as well as other APC member countries.
(Vietnam-APC Membership)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- About 20,000 Hungarian Holocaust survivors are
expected to receive a support of 400 U.S. dollars each from a
Swiss Fund, a press release in Bern reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rolf Bloch, President of the Swiss Fund for Needy Victims of
the Holocaust, handed over the support money Thursday to a group
of survivor representatives in a ceremony in Budapest, Hungary.
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 Hungarian victims have already received such a
grant, says a press release. (Holocaust Victims-Swiss-Fund)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- United States researchers have found that
genetically engineered, chemotherapy-resistant tumor cells may be
an effective weapon against ovarian cancer.
</P>
<P>
Researchers from two U.S. universities have found that the
cells can express a "suicide gene", which renders sensitivity to a
new drug, resulting in the killing of tumor cells.
</P>
<P>
So far the experimental treatment has reduced ovarian cancer in
laboratory mice and has not shown any harmful effects in women.
</P>
<P>
Researchers from Tulane University said the next step was a
broad study testing its effectiveness against ovarian cancer in
women.  (US-Cancer-Killer)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Secretary of State for Northern Ireland
Marjorie Mowlam said Friday the Irish Republican Army was involved
in two murders this week.
</P>
<P>
The region's police chief, Ronnie Flanagan, "has given me a
full briefing on the murders of Brendan Campbell and Robert
Dougan, along with his assessment that the IRA were involved in
these murders," Mowlam said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The two men were gunned down in Belfast on Monday and Tuesday
separately, casting a shadow on the fragile peace process.
(Britain-IRA-Killings)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- A senior United Nations official said here on
Wednesday that better financial disclosure by commercial banks
might have given some early warning signals on the financial
crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Rubens Ricupero, Secretary-general of the UN Conference on
Trade and Development (UNCTAD), was speaking at a meeting of the
UNCTAD Intergovernmental Working Group of Experts on International
Standards of Accounting and Reporting (ISAR). (Asia-Crisis)
</P>
<P>
