<HEADLINE> Zhang Wannian Meets Netherlands Guest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese military
officer said today that Chinese Premier Li Peng's forthcoming
visit to the Netherlands will contribute greatly to the friendly
cooperative relations between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Gen. Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the Chinese Central
Military Commission (CMC), made the remarks during a meeting at
the Great Hall of the People in Beijing with Gen. Van Den Breeman,
chief of the Netherlands Defense Staff.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that China and the Netherlands share many things in
common, though they have different social systems, adding their
peoples have contributed to the world development.
</P>
<P>
Advancing bilateral ties not only comforms to the basic
interests of the two peoples, but also serves world peace and
stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two armed forces have enjoyed sound relations in recent
years, said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
China's armed forces maintain a positive attitude toward the
development of ties between the two sides, according to Zhang. He
expressed his conviction that Gen. Van Den Breeman's tour will
promote the in-depth development of relations between the two
armed forces in extensive areas.
</P>
<P>
Gen. Van Den Breeman recounted his meetings with senior Chinese
military officers during the ongoing visist and said that the
contacts have laid a solid foundation for enhancing understanding
and cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He said he follows with interest the development of relations
between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Lieut. Gen. Xiong Guangkai, Deputy Chief of General Staff of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army, was present at the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
