<HEADLINE> Three Nepalese Die of Rabies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of rabies has
claimed three lives in Terhathum district of eastern Nepal, the
official RSS news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 30 people and some cattle have been affected by the
epidemic, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Due to lack of rabies vaccine at the local hospital, only eight
of the affected have been vaccinated. The rest have been sent to
other district hospitals for treatment, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
As stray dogs roam the streets across the country, rabies
breaks out now and then.  
</P>
