<HEADLINE> Stocks Plunge in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stock prices plunged with
the key Nikkei index falling below the 17,000 mark Friday due to
growing skepticism over the government's economy-boosting measures.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the first section
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange tumbled 383.92 points, or 2.24 percent
from Thursday's close to 16,791.01.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, declined 18.16 points, or 1.40
percent to 1,280.54.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section dropped to an estimated 630 million
shares from Thursday's 731.05 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Traders said investors began to unwind their buying positions
because of lack of fresh news to brighten the economic outlook
during recent sessions.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outpaced gainers 942 to 243, with 94 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
