<HEADLINE> Charity Federation Donates Houses for Use as Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- China's largest charity
organization will donate 800,000 yuan worth of makeshift houses to
schools in quake-hit Zhangjiakou, ensuring the scheduled start of
the new semester, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The 100 sets of houses will be sent to Zhangbei County, the
most seriously damaged area, said Wu Jianguo, vice-president of
the China Charity Federation (CCF).
</P>
<P>
The chilly winter interferes with the construction of long-term
buildings until May. But the schools are scheduled to start the
new term on March 1.
</P>
<P>
After installing the makeshift houses, the CCF will prepare for
the reconstruction of school structures and welfare houses for the
elderly, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
During the week after the catastrophic tremor on January 10, the
CCF collected 1.5 million yuan (180,000 U.S. dollars) for the
victims.
</P>
<P>
The CCF put aside another 4.9 million yuan in donations for
rehabilitation. 
</P>
