<DOCNO> XIE19980213.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Genetically-Engineered Cells Kill Ovarian Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 12 (Xinhua) -- United States researchers
have found that genetically engineered, chemotherapy-resistant
tumor cells may be an effective weapon against ovarian cancer.
</P>
<P>
Researchers from two U.S. universities have found that the
cells can express a "suicide gene", which renders sensitivity to a
new drug, resulting in the killing of tumor cells.
</P>
<P>
So far the experimental treatment has reduced ovarian cancer in
laboratory mice and has not shown any harmful effects in women.
</P>
<P>
Researchers from Tulane University said the next step was a
broad study testing its effectiveness against ovarian cancer in
women.
</P>
<P>
For the treatment, scientists created a vaccine using gene
therapy, a method that has already been used successfully on some
other diseases.
</P>
<P>
In a laboratory the researchers attached part of an
ovarian-cancer gene to a gene from the herpes virus.The result, a
so-called "suicide gene", is injected into the patient's abdomen.
</P>
<P>
There, it seems to affect the other ovarian cancer genes so
that when a doctor treats the patient with a standard herpes drug,
the woman's immune system also attacks the cancer cells.
</P>
<P>
Ovarian cancer is the most lethal female malignancy in the
United States. Last year, the disease occurred in about 26,000
women and was the cause of 14,000 reported deaths.
</P>
<P>
In most cases, when ovarian cancer is first diagnosed, the
disease has already spread, leading to a five-year survival of 30
percent of victims.
</P>
<P>
This week, the researchers presented their study to a
conference of the Society of Gynecologic Oncologists, the only
U.S.-based medical organization dedicated to the treatment of
female cancers.
</P>
<P>
As part of their study, the researchers tested the injection on
18 women, all in the final stages of ovarian cancer, who had not
responded to other treatment.Cancer levels in four of them
improved and the disease completely disappeared in another.
</P>
<P>
Right now doctors have no reliable test for ovarian
cancer. Some women report symptoms, but they are mild and easily
mistaken for other maladies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980213.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Says IRA Involves in Killings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 13 (Xinhua) -- British Secretary of State for
Northern Ireland Marjorie Mowlam said Friday the Irish Republican
Army was involved in two murders this week.
</P>
<P>
The region's police chief, Ronnie Flanagan, "has given me a
full briefing on the murders of Brendan Campbell and Robert
Dougan, along with his assessment that the IRA were involved in
these murders," Mowlam said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The two men were gunned down in Belfast on Monday and Tuesday
separately, casting a shadow on the fragile peace process.
</P>
<P>
"This will now have to be considered very carefully with the
Irish government and the other parties in accordance with the
proper procedures," she added.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of talks, which involve both British and Irish
governments and eight Protestant and Catholic parties, any party
which has a guerrilla wing actively engaged in violence can be
expelled.
</P>
<P>
"The integrity of the talks process and the commitment to
exclusively peaceful means are paramount and all parties must be
treated fairly and equally," Mowlam said.
</P>
<P>
The IRA declared a ceasefire last July, thus enabling its
political wing Sinn Fein to gain a seat in the multi-party peace
talks that began last September.
</P>
<P>
It is thought likely that Sinn Fein will be temporarily
expelled from the talks for the involvement in the two killings.
</P>
<P>
The Ulster Democratic Party, a pro-British party, has already
been expelled from the peace process recently for links with a
paramilitary group which was responsible for a number of murders.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
