<HEADLINE> HK Population Up 3 Percent in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The estimated population of
Hong Kong at the end of 1997 was 6,617,100, representing a 3
percent increase compared with a year ago, local Census and
Statistics Department said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The overall population density per sq km was over 6,000,
making Hong Kong one of the most densely populated places in the
world.
</P>
<P>
The balance of arrivals and departures showed a net inflow of
some 167,700 persons in 1997, constituting 86 percent of the
population growth.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, there were 59,400 births and 31,300
deaths in Hong Kong. The natural increase amounted to 28,100,
accounting for 14 percent of the population growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
