<HEADLINE> UN, ICRC Appeal for 2.5M Dollars in Emergency Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations and the
International Committee for Red Cross (ICRC) Friday launched an
appeal for 2.5 million dollars in emergency relief assistance for
the quake-hit northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The appeal called upon the world community to donate emergency
aid needed for the shelterless people of Rostaq, one of the
worst-hit districts of Takhar province, a report by the Associated
Press of Pakistan quoted a spokesperson for the United Nations as
saying here.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson said that the quake-hit districts have been
hit by harsh weather, and rescue and relief operations have been
seriously hampered due to heavy snow.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations and international aid agencies could not
airlift assistance to northern Afghanistan Wednesday because of
inclement weather, said the spokesperson.
</P>
<P>
However, more relief assistance for the quake-affected people
was in the pipeline and would be despatched to northern
Afghanistan as soon as weather conditions improve there, the
spokesperson added.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6.1 on the Richter scale hit
Afghanistan's Takhar province last week, which left more than
4,000 people dead and thousands of others homeless.  
</P>
</TEXT>
