<HEADLINE> Pakistan Offers Investment Choices in Communications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government is
offering choices to local and foreign investors to invest in
communications projects, Communications Minister Azam Hoti said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hoti was talking to visiting Turkish Maritime Affairs Minister
Burhan Kara, who is leading a delegation to a meeting of the
Pak-Turkish Joint Ministerial Commission, according to the
Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting the two ministers exchanged views on matters
pertaining to further cooperation in the communications sector.
</P>
<P>
Hoti said that Pakistan welcomes Turkish investors to take
advantage of the conducive climate in the country based on
investment-friendly policies adopted by the government.
</P>
<P>
Noting Pakistan and Turkey enjoy cordial and special ties based
on common religion, brotherhood and mutual understanding, Hoti
said that Turkish companies have been playing a tremendous role in
the development and prosperity of Pakistan through cooperation in
various socio-economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
He further said that the government is expanding and modifying
the existing communications system to face challenges of the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
This agenda envisages modification of telecommunications
system, ports shipping, inland navigation system and construction
of a network of motorways, he added.
</P>
<P>
Expressing gratitude to the hospitality of the Pakistani
government, Turkish Maritime Affairs Minister Burhan Kara said
that relations between Turkey and Pakistan are blooming day by
day.
</P>
<P>
Turkish investors would like to benefit from investment
opportunities in the communications sector of Pakistan, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
