<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Province Expands Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 value of the animal
husbandry sector in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region accounted for 32 percent of the region's total agricultural
output.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that the province's meat output climbed
6.9 percent to 140,000 tons for the year. The output of eggs was
48,000 tons, up 2.4 percent; milk, 210,000 tons, up 25.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Some 32,000 households specialize in raising livestock, such as
cattle, sheep and pigs. And the region has built seven pig farms,
and five sheep and eight cattle ranches to promote the large-scale
production of animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
To seek and expand marketing opportunities for animal
husbandry, Ningxia has formed large slaughterhouses and wholesale
markets in some major areas of the region. Some livestock products
were exported to European countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the region has raised more than 14 kinds of
special livestock, including pigeons, foxes and snakes with a
value reaching 500 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
