<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province to Cooperate with Motorola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- A Sichuan-Motorola cooperation
committee was established recently in Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
Song Baorui, governor of Sichuan Province, and Richard Younts,
senior vice- president of Motorola, are co-chairmen of the
committee.
</P>
<P>
At the first working conference of the committee, deputy
governor Li Dachang of Sichuan outlined the development and
investment environment of the province. Both sides said they are
satisfied and confident with the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between the province and Motorola began in 1995,
when Motorola set up its first joint venture, a semiconductor
factory in Leshan city.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the state planning commission, about 225 million
U.S. dollars will be spent on the third-phase expansion of the
factory to make it the largest semiconductor producer in southwest
China.
</P>
<P>
Motorola is one of the world's major producers of radio
communications equipment, semiconductors, and electronics
equipment. 
