<HEADLINE> East China City Having Warmest Spring Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, the capital of east
China's Zhejiang Province, today recorded a daytime temperature of
27 degrees Centigrade, the highest in spring in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
This is announced by the Meteorological Bureau of the city.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou has had higher than normal temperatures since last
weekend. Now, many residents are seen in summer clothing, out
enjoying the warm air in parks.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists say that temperatures are expected to return to
normal in a couple of days when a cold front from the north hits
this part of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
