<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Property Market Has Robust Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai had a robust
property market in 1997 with total transaction volume hitting 10
billion yuan (1.2 billion U.S. dollars), doubling the previous
year's figure, according to an official from the Shanghai Real
Estate Trading Center.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Hailong, president of the center, said more than 500
property traders were involved in last year's real estate market.
</P>
<P>
The center, established three years ago, has played an
important role in developing Shanghai's property market. The badly
operated Shanghai Lihua Automobile Leasing Co., for instance, was
sold through the center at 18.1 million yuan, some 10 million
yuan higher than the offering price.
</P>
<P>
The center has registered 870 Shanghai enterprises and 242
companies in such inland provinces as Qinghai, Sichuan and
Hunan. They cover businesses from plantation, forestry, textiles
and chemicals to transportation, food processing, machinery and
catering. Total registered capital in 1997 was 5.7 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The center also serves as a consultant to aid enterprises in
market competition, property transfers, mortgages, leasing and
intermediate transaction services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
