<HEADLINE> China to Fund Publishing of Academic Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- China will appropriate three
million yuan (360,000 U.S. dollars) to publish 62 kinds of
academic works on science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The committee of the National Science and Technology Academic
Works Fund announced here today the first group of publishing
programs to receive annual financial support.
</P>
<P>
Publishing houses are expected to receive 20,000-to-100,000
yuan (2,400-to-12,000 U.S. dollars) for publishing each of the
books on the list.
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Science and Technology Commission
(SSTC) said that the fund was established last May with 30 million
yuan (3.6 million U.S. dollars) from the Ministry of Finance and
the SSTC to aid in publishing outstanding academic works.
</P>
<P>
In China, many scientists and researchers have been unable to
publish their works for lack of funding.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Wei, deputy head of the fund committee, noted that the 62
types of works cover mathematics, chemistry, life sciences, earth
sciences, materials and engineering science, and the information
field. More than 40 percent of the works to be funded deal with
life-science research.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the eldest author is 85 years old whereas the
youngest is 33; and 14 are academicians from the Chinese Academy
of Sciences and Chinese Academy of Engineering.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Zhu welcomes donations from both domestic and
overseas ventures, organizations and individuals for publishing
academic works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
