<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Builds Large Wine Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- A large grape wine producing
center has been built in Mile County, southwest China's Yunnan
Province, in cooperation with Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The center is expected to produce more than 4,000 tons of wine
this year and the output will reach 50,000 tons by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The center now has 1,300 hectares of vineyard, which will be
expanded to more than 3,300 ha by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The wine center produces wine with advanced technology from
France, the world's famous wine-maker.
</P>
<P>
Mile is famous for its karst topography and good sunshine,
slight rainfall, and sandy loam, good natural conditions for
growing grape.
</P>
<P>
The grape and wine industry has been listed as one of the 18
projects to exploit resources in Yunnan, and is considered
important to helping local farmers shake off poverty.  
</P>
