<HEADLINE> North China's Hebei Starts Off '98 Tourism Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province kicked off tourism programs for the year 1998 featuring a
"city and country tour" by organizing colorful performances in
different cities to celebrate Lantern Festival on Feb. 11.
</P>
<P>
Local tourism authorities said that this year they would
continue to offer 12 different programs to overseas tourists, but
with more content.
</P>
<P>
Construction of facilities for skiing and hunting tours in
Zhangjiakou and in Chengde has been undertaken and is expected to
be ready for use by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province has also arranged a group of gala activities to
entertain tourists, including the China Tourism and Art Festival
in Xianghe County in May, the Water World Holiday and
Pleasure-Seeking Festival at Baiyangdian Lake and the
International Tourism Festival at Chengde in June, an
international boxing meeting in Yongnian County in August, as well
as a skiing competition with the participation of at least 10,000
people in December.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the province will cooperate closely with
Beijing and Tianjin in exploring the tourism market and will put
forward more tourist programs closer to those two cities to
attract more overseas tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
