<HEADLINE> Motorola to Enhance Presence in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Motorola signed a memorandum
of understanding this week on establishing a cooperation committee
with Sichuan Province to enhance its presence in the high-tech
development of southwest China, according to sources with Motorola
(China) Electronics Ltd..
</P>
<P>
Song Baorui, governor of Sichuan Province, and Richard Younts,
senior vice present of Motorola, were elected co-chairmen of the
committee.
</P>
<P>
At the committee's first work conference, which was held on
Feb. 11, both the Chinese and U.S. partners approved an investment
plan to expand the production scale of Leshan-Phoenix
Semiconductor Company, a Sino-Motorola joint venture in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Founded in February of 1995, Leshan-Phoenix is the first joint
venture by Motorola in China. Under the investors' agreement, the
venture will absorb an additional 225 million U.S. dollars for the
third-phase expansion project there. In addition, Motorola has
promised to continue its technology transfer to develop the
venture into the largest semiconductor production base in
southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU of Motorola and Sichuan Province, Motorola will
launch an R&AMP;D center in southwest China, purchase more parts from
local enterprises, and accelerate the localization drive in its
joint venture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
