<HEADLINE> Sino-German Joint Venture Exporting Car Parts to Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The First Automotive
Works-Volkswagen Co. Ltd., a Sino-German joint venture in the city
of Changchun, a car manufacturing center in China's Jilin
Province, will export a second group of automobile parts to
Germany this year, according to a contract signed here recently.
</P>
<P>
The corporation sold 15,000 cylinders to Germany last year, and
this year will supply 100,000 connecting rods, 100,000 camshafts,
100,000 crankshafts, 60,000 cylinder heads, and 21,000
cylinders. All products have been approved by the Volkswagen Group.
</P>
<P>
The First Automotive Works-Volkswagen Co. was built at a cost of
10.7 billion yuan. Its engine plant is supplied with imported
equipment and has an annual production capacity of 270,000
engines. 
</P>
