<HEADLINE> Vietnam Becomes Full Member of ASEAN Promotion Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February, 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam became a full member of
the ASEAN Promotion Center (APC) on Thursday, Vietnam News Agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese ambassador to Japan, Nguyen Quoc Dzung, signed an
agreement in Tokyo Thursday on Vietnam's joining in the APC, which
was established in 1980 by ASEAN member countries and Japan under
the Japanese government's initiative and assistance.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the signing ceremony, Ngyuen Quoc Dzung said he
believed that Vietnam's joining in the APC would further promote
its relations with Japan as well as other APC member countries.
</P>
<P>
In Jakarta on the same day, Vietnamese ambassador to Indonesia
Nguyen Dang Quang also signed an agreement on the country's
participation in the APC. The signing was witnessed by ASEAN
General-Secretary Rodolfo C. Severino.
</P>
<P>
The APC now has seven full members: Brunei, Indonesia,
Malaysia, the Philippines, Thailand, Vietnam and Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
