<HEADLINE> China Building Garden Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, February 13 (Xinhua) -- China now has 12 cities
referred to as garden cities, with more than 35 percent of their
areas planted with trees and shrubs.
</P>
<P>
The country began its garden city program in 1992. The twelve
cities all have six sq. m. of greenery per resident.
</P>
<P>
For the more harmonious development of cities and their
environment, central China's Hubei Province has emphasized the
planting of trees in cities, and some of its historic cities like
Wuhan, Yichang and Xiangfan have gone about it in a thorough way.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan, capital of Hubei province, now has 6.78 sq.m. of greenery
every person. The city has also built 21 parks of various
types and 240 small gardens. Wuhan will also formulat more
regulations on pollution control and tree planting.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, Hubei has planted trees on
150,000 hectares of land, completing 70 percent of the
year's tree planting goal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
