<HEADLINE> Singapore Appoints New CEO for Suzhou Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore government
announced on Friday that it had appointed a new Chief Executive
Officer (CEO) of the China-Singapore Suzhou Industrial Park
Development Company Ltd (CSSD), effective from March 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Trade and Industry and the Jurong Town
Corporation (JTC) said in a statement that Major-General Lim Neo
Chian, now Chairman of the JTC, has been appointed the CEO of the
CSSD and the Singapore Suzhou Township Development Co. Pte Ltd
(SSTD) to replace, David Lim, out-going CEO of the CSSD and SSTD.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, Major-General Lim will continue the
program initiated by David Lim to lead the CSSD in developing the
Suzhou Industrial Park into a world-class industrial park in
China. It noted that as at January 1998, a total of 2.7 billion US
dollars of investments have been committed to the park.
</P>
<P>
The CSSD is the joint venture between the SSTD and Suzhou
Industrial Park Co Ltd (SIPC) to develop the Suzhou Industrial
Park. SIPC, the Chinese consortium, has 35 percent equity while
SSTD, the Singapore consortium, owns 65 percent equity in the
CSSD.  
</P>
