<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Leading Other Autonomous Regions In GDP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region produced a GDP of slightly over 200 billion yuan
in 1997, ranking first among China's five autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has 46 million people, more than the total of the other
four -- Tibet, Xinjiang, Ningxia, and Inner Mongolia -- combined.
</P>
<P>
For the past few years, Guangxi has achieved one of the fastest
economic growth rates, with a policy supporting economic growth
and keeping population growth below the state level.
</P>
<P>
It continued to stay on to develop such major products as
sugar, fruits, vegetables, livestocks, aquatic products, tea, and
herbal medicines, and applied more agronomics and technologies in
this effort.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Guangxi also encouraged township enterprises to
promote reforms, and improve or try new management systems in an
effort to revitalize the sector and contribute more to local
agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the region produced 16.6 million tons of grain
last year, 30 million tons of sugarcane, three million tons of
fruit, 3.13 million tons of meat, and 1.9 million tons of aquatic
products, increases as high as 25 percent in some cases.
</P>
<P>
The modern enterprise system it put into force on a larger
trial basis has considerably enhanced enterprises' market
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The region has also made some headway in reforming state
enterprises, and has begun to shift industrial development to
foodstuff, nonferrous metals, new technology, and other pillar
industries for new economic growth areas.
</P>
<P>
Consequently, this effort has helped revert the downhill trend
of the state industrial sector. Last year, Guangxi had 67.5
billion yuan in industrial added value, a year-on-year rise of 8
percent.
</P>
<P>
It spent 52.4 billion yuan on fixed assets, a 10 percent
increase, considerably improving its infrastructure in the
process. The completion of major projects like the Nanning-Kunming
Railway improved its investment environment also.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
