<HEADLINE> Philippines, Spain to Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 13 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos said the
Philippines and Spain should further strengthen their relations,
especially in the field of investment and trade, a presidential
press release said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The press release said Ramos made the remarks Thursday night at
a dinner hosted for him and First Lady Amelita Ramos by King Juan
Carlos and Queen Sofia who were visiting the country.
</P>
<P>
