newly-found business opportunities to further reinvigorate our
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the area of development assistance, Ramos acknowledged
Spain's commitment of 30 million U.S. dollars for projects and
programs on poverty alleviation, human resources development,
technology transfer and the peace process in Mindanao, the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
He added that Spain will assist in the restoration and
preservation of buildings, churches, forts, bridges, ancestral
homes and other historical landmarks in different parts of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines declared independence from Spain's
three-century colonial rule on June 12, 1898.  
