<HEADLINE> China's Fashion Capital Gets New Fashion Magazine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Fashion magazines are in
vogue in China these days, and the latest entry to the publishing
world is one that appeared recently in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The magazine 'How' is a reincarnation of the earlier 'Culture
and Life' which was published for nearly 20 years. It gives its
Chinese readers a taste of the latest fashions around the world.
</P>
<P>
Fashionable and popular clothing, jewelry, cosmetics, and
perfumes can all be found on the magazine's pages, according to
its publisher.
</P>
<P>
'Culture and Life' started in January, 1979 and had a press run
of three million at its height. But, it was decided that the name
should be changed and that it should have a greater market share,
according to its former editor-in-chief Hao Mingjian.
</P>
<P>
However, the new bimonthly will face some stiff competition
from seven other fashion magazines available like
Beijing's 'Look', Guangzhou's 'New Age Illustrated', and 'Elle',
China's first fashion magazine, which appeared a decade
ago. 
</P>
