<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Visits Infrastructure Projects in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
said Friday that he was impressed by the rapid infrastructural
development in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Qiao and his wife Yu Wen visited infrastructure projects here
Friday morning in the company of Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and his wife Betty
Tung.
</P>
<P>
They made a tour of a container terminal in Kwai Chung, the
2.2-km Tsing Ma Bridge, the world's longest railway-highway
suspension bridge, and the new airport at Chek Lap Kok which is
scheduled to go into operation in July.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that Hong Kong is an international financial, trade,
shipping, tourist and information center and its great economic
achievements attracts worldwide attention. Infrastructural
construction has grown rapidly in recent years, laying a solid
foundation for Hong Kong's long-term prosperity and development.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that the SAR government under the leadership of Tung
Chee Hwa will surely bring Hong Kong's various advantages into
full play to further enhance its economic competitiveness and
maintain and promote Hong Kong's economic prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao came to Hong Kong Tuesday for a five-day visit. He has met
with Hong Kong deputies to the Eighth and Ninth NPC, principal
officials of the SAR government, members of the Executive Council
and the Provisional Legislative Council as well as local public
figures.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to leave for Beijing Saturday.  
</P>
