<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets Brother of Indonesian Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo met here today with Probosutejo, brother of Indonesian
President Suharto.
</P>
<P>
Probosutejo is a well-known banker and entrepreneur in
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Zhongnanhai, headquarters of the
central government, Wu said that China has always paid attention
to the economic crisis in Southeast Asia and the economic
situation of Indonesia. He said that China is sympathetic to
Indonesia's fiscal difficulties.
</P>
<P>
However, China believes that the difficulties are temporary
ones, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that, after the pending general
election, Indonesia would restore and develop its economy at a
faster rate and would quickly overcome its financial difficulties
through its own efforts and help from the International Monetary
Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
Wu said the Chinese government has offered assistance within
its capacity to Indonesia under the IMF framework. He said that
China's commitment on non-depreciation of its currency supports
other Southeast Asian economies.
</P>
<P>
Probosutejo said that China's economic growth and the stability
it showed in the face of the Southeast Asia economic crisis was
impressive.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that China would continue to assist
Indonesia's efforts to rehabilitate its economy and further
promote mutually beneficial economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Indonesian government would stick to the
"one China" policy and would not have any official links with
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Probosutejo is here at the invitation of the Chinese People's
Institute of Foreign Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
