<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Programs Help Rural Economy In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Since east China's Zhejiang
Province started the Spark Plan, a technological program, in 1986,
it has witnessed a rapid growth in agriculture and farmers'
training.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year the 5,500 programs, which have the
purpose of industrializing agriculture and improving
township-level enterprises, have produced 80 billion yuan (9.6
billion U.S. dollars) in output value, 15 billion yuan in pre-tax
profits, and 1.8 billion U.S. dollars worth of export earnings for
the province.
</P>
<P>
The greater use of science and technology in the province's 150
villages in recent years has provided training for 1.3 million
people.
</P>
<P>
Now each of the 150 pilot township enterprises has an annual
output value exceeding 100 million yuan and profits of more than a
million yuan. The province's 400 export-oriented companies each
have annual sales of at least 500,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
