<HEADLINE> Germany Win Luge Men's Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 13 (Xinhua) -- German pair Stefan Krausse
and Jan Behrendt sprinted to win the title of the men's luge doubles
event at the 18th Olympic Winter Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The German duo collected one minutes and 41.105 seconds for the
title, beating American pair Chris Thorpe and Gordy Sheer to the
second by 0.022 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Another American pair Mark Grimmette and Brian Martin finished
third at 1:41.217. 
</P>
