<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty Drive In China's Poorest Region Paying Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, February 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 300,000 poor people
in China's Shanxi Province got away from poverty in 1997, a local
government official said here recently.
</P>
<P>
They live in 451 villages in the Luliang Mountain area, one of
18 very poor regions in China.
</P>
<P>
The number of people living below the poverty line (an annual
income of less than 500 yuan) in Shanxi has dropped to fewer than
500,000, and the provincial government is determined to help
improve the lives of all of these remaining impoverished people by
the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Officials at all levels played an important role in the poverty
drive. Zhang Luxu, the deputy Party secretary of Luliang
Prefecture, assisted Xinyi Township in building 10 ha of
greenhouses and in importing modern agronomic techniques. As a
result, each farm household in the township earned 10,000 yuan
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
