<HEADLINE> Computers Helping Chinese Farmers Make More Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Officials of Yanting County in
southwest China's Sichuan Province have found a convenient way to
get more detailed information about specific rural households.
</P>
<P>
The tool they're using is the computer at the county
Information Center, which holds background information on more
than 50,000 rural families and helps the county government make
decisions about how best to help farmers.
</P>
<P>
County and township officials have a responsibility to help
poor families get away from poverty, and their contacts and
successes are logged into computers as one way to assess their
work.
</P>
<P>
A year of this specific method has proven helpful. The village
of Shiqiao is one example. Out of 388 households, 312 have reached
the standard of a comfortably well-off life, and they say they
think the computers have a role in this. 
</P>
</TEXT>
