<HEADLINE> Malaria Plaguing More People in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The number of malaria
sufferers has been on the rise in Mozambique in the passing
month, almost quadrupling the number in the same period last
year, an official with the Ministry of Health said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Samuel Mbunda, director of the Malaria Sector of the Ministry
of Health, was quoted by the Noticias as saying Thursday that
about 700 malaria patients are registered in Maputo and the
suburban Matola a week.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rain is claimed to be the cause for the outbreak of
the plague, Mbunda said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has mapped out an emergency plan to spray
mosquito killer medicine in Maputo and its suburban areas, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 800 were reported killed by the infectious disease, and
some 1500 plagued last year, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
