<HEADLINE> Austrian Wins Men's Combined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Mario Reiter
claimed the title of the men's combined event at the 18th Olympic
Winter Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian, who led the slalom event with 1.81 seconds over
Norwegian Lasse Kjus, won the title after finishing sixth in the
downhill event with one minute and 36.21 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Reiter aggregated a total of three minutes and 8.06 seconds for the
title, beating Kjus to the silver medal podium at 3:08.65.
</P>
<P>
It was the second silver medal that Kjus won on Friday after he
came second in the men's downhill event earlier today.
</P>
<P>
Another Austrian Christian Mayer was third in the combined, with an
aggregated time of 3:10.11.
</P>
<P>
Hermann Maier of Austria, who was crashed in the men's downhill
event, did not start in the combined downhill. 
</P>
