<HEADLINE> Pakistan Prime Minister Meets Chinese Dignitaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Pakistan Prime
Minister Mohammad Nawaz Sharif met this morning with Chinese
dignitaries from diplomatic, press and cultural communities here
just before departing for Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
Among the 90 people invited were He Luli, vice chairwoman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, and Pakistani visitors accompanying
Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Sharif and He both spoke at the breakfast.
</P>
<P>
Sharif spoke highly of the Pakistan-China friendship and
briefed the dignitaries on Pakistan's domestic and foreign
policies.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that Pakistan and China are old
friends, and "our time-tested friendship has remained strong,
vibrant and durable and mutual cooperation in various fields is
flourishing despite new developments in the regional and global
scenario and in the face of multiple pressures."
</P>
<P>
Sharif pointed out that his country "firmly supports China in
all its just causes including the issues of Taiwan, Tibet and
human rights."
</P>
<P>
China will continue to play an important role in promoting
peace and stability in the region, said Sharif, adding that "a
strong and prosperous China is a guarantee for peace, security and
stability not only in our region but also in the world at large.
</P>
<P>
"We will constantly strive to usher in a partnership of
cooperation between our two countries into the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani prime minister also answered questions raised by
Chinese scholars and experts.
</P>
<P>
He Luli said that China and Pakistan are close neighbors, and
bilateral beneficial cooperation based on mutual trust has had a
sound and smooth growth since the two countries established
diplomatic relations 47 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have also cooperated fruitfully and effectively
in politics, the economy and trade, science and technology and
culture, she said. The Sino-Pakistani good-neighbor friendship
sets an example for state-to-state relations with different social
systems, she added.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China will always be a trustworthy and reliable
friend of Pakistan no matter what changes may take place in the
international situation, she said: "We hope and believe that
through joint efforts from the two governments and their people,
bilateral cooperation in various fields will be further deepened
and bilateral relations will continue to be consolidated and
strengthened."  
</P>
