<HEADLINE> Bank Profits Up In Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The Hebei Branch of
China's Construction Bank made 560 million yuan in profits for
1997, more than double of the 1996 figure, a bank official said.
</P>
<P>
The branch loaned 6.3 billion yuan to 99 key enterprises and
projects in power, transportation, telecommunications, civil
aviation, and railways, accounting for 86 percent of loans
approved for 1997.
</P>
<P>
It also has loan deals with five large enterprises like the
Tangshan Rolling Stock Plant and Liantong Company.
</P>
<P>
To cut financial risks to a minimum, local banks evaluated 5.7
billion yuan in loans for 186 projects, 51 of which, involving 630
million yuan, were vetoed after further study.
</P>
<P>
The branch increased its market competition by a more judicious
use of loans and raising the discount rate.
</P>
<P>
With its new provincial computer network, the bank has issued
219,000 Dragon Cards, which have done 15 billion yuan in
business.  
</P>
</TEXT>
