<HEADLINE> Three-Tiered Transportation Network In Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning, a leading Chinese
industrial base, has spent more than 2 billion yuan on a
three-tiered highway, ship, and air network
</P>
<P>
It built 4,000 km of expressways from Shenyang, the provincial
capital, to the port city of Dalian, and to the cities of Tieling,
Fushun, and Benxi. Eight of the province's cities now have access
to expressways.
</P>
<P>
The addition of 15 berths at the second-grade harbor zone last
year brought the number of berths in Liaoning to more than 100,
giving it one of the largest harbor areas in China and the largest
cargo handling capacity .
</P>
<P>
It has aviation centers in the cities of Shenyang, Dalian,
Dandong, and Chaoyang. Shenyang's China Northern Airlines has
increased its air routes to 150, going to 50 cities inside and
outside China. Three new air routes from Shenyang to Japanese
cities are expected to open soon.  
