<HEADLINE> 1998 AAAS Annual Meeting Opens in Philadelphia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philadelphia, February 12 (Xinhua)--The 98' Annual Meeting and
Science Innovation Exposition as well as the celeberation of the
150th anniversary for American Association of Advancement of
Science (AAAS), were officially opened here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Among the some 5000 participants from all walks of life, there
are also many prominent scientists, policy makers, industry
executives, teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
In her key note speech, AAAS president and 1998 Meeting Program
Chairman Mildred S. Dresselhaus said, the theme for the 1998
Meeting -- Exploring Frontiers and Expanding Opportunities-- sets
the tone for a unique blend of symposia, topical and plenary
lectures, specialized seminars and poster presentations.
</P>
<P>
During it's week-long sessions, some 850 papers in 18 areas of
science and technology will be presented by their authors, apart
from 100 exhibits, students science posters and public science day.
</P>
<P>
The AAAS, founded 150 years ago in Philadelphia by 87
outstanding American scientists, now has 145,000 members from
around the world. Except holding annunal meeting enable
scientists to report their new discovery, breakthroughs and
archivements in science and technology, It also makes efforts to
promote public understanding of science and enchance cooperation
among scientists within and outside the United States of
America. 
</P>
