<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Bjarte Engen Vik
sailed ito the lead after the first day of the men's individual Nordic
combined, with a total of 241 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian, World Cup leader, leaped 89.5 and 94.5 meters in two
jumps under the clear sky at the 90m normal hill in Hakuba and will
start Saturday's 15-kilometer race 36 seconds ahead of second place
Velerij Stoljarov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Stoljarov, who led the first round with 92.5 meters, held on for
second place with 235 points after a leap of 89.5 meters in the second
round.
</P>
<P>
