Kenji Ogiwara, placed third with 232.5 points.
</P>
<P>
Vik, bronze medalist at the last Olympics in Lillehammer, Norway
four years ago, was satisfied with the results. He said:"The result
is better than I hoped in dreams... I knew I could do well in the
jumps but to win the jumping here is very good."
</P>
<P>
"Tomorrow is another competition. I knew my chances are good but
it's not over. It's been a long time since I competed in a cross
country race so I'm not so sure about my shape," he added. 
