<HEADLINE> S.Lanka Exhibition Draws Record Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The grand exhibition featuring
Sri Lanka's progress and achievements since its independence 50
years ago has attracted a record number of visitors since it
opened on February 5, organizers said Friday.
</P>
<P>
By Thursday, more than 514,000 people had visited the
exhibition in the center of Colombo, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
More visitors are expected to view the exhibition on weekends.
</P>
<P>
A total of 939 stalls are displaying all kinds of products or
models from locally manufactured milk to aircraft of the Sri Lanka
Air Force. About 479 stalls are sponsored by the government while
the rest by private companies.
</P>
<P>
Each day the exhibition closes late around midnight in order to
enable those working in the day time to go to the exhibition after
work.
</P>
<P>
However, a large number of visitors have complained of the
absence of a guide map at the entrance, which made it difficult
for them to go to the stalls they were interested in.
</P>
<P>
In response to the complaints, the organizers have decided to
put up some indicators within the next few days.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is a major part of the country's celebration
activities for the 50th Independence Day, which was on February 4.
The exhibition will conclude on February 20.
</P>
<P>
A large number of security personnel have been positioned in
and around the exhibition venue.  
</P>
