<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Surround 600 LTTE Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Government troops involved in
Operation Jayasikuru (Certain of Victory) had surrounded about 600
Tamil rebels in Mankulam town in Northern Sri Lanka, the official
newspaper Daily News reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a spokesman for the Northern Brigade Command
as saying that the siege followed days of fierce fighting between
the two sides along the Mullaitivu jungle and Mankulam, both of
strategic importance for military operations.
</P>
<P>
The "strong contingent of terrorists" who continued their
mortar fire since Tuesday on Jayasikuru troops, had stopped their
fire from dawn Thursday, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said that was a clear indication that the troops had
effectively prevented any rebel reinforcement from reaching the
trapped rebels. The rebels were also badly in need of food and
ammunitions, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ground troops halted their operation on Thursday afternoon
while the Air Force continued bombardment at rebel positions.
</P>
<P>
There has been heavy fighting in the north since the beginning
of the month.
</P>
<P>
On February 1, the troops said they killed more than 300 rebels
in Kilinochchi, Northern Province when the Tigers launched a
sudden attack.
</P>
<P>
Fighting along the Kilinochchi defense line continued the
following days as government troops tried to regain a section of
the one kilometer defense line lost to the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Security forces on Thursday also attacked a truck carrying 11
Tamil rebels north of Mankulam, killing all of them and destroying
the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have
been fighting for a separate state of their own in the north and
east of the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
Most of the major battles in recent months were reported in the
north, where troops of Jayasikuru Operation have been moving inch
by inch in the northern jungle area since last May, trying to open
a land route to the Jaffna peninsula.  
</P>
</TEXT>
