<HEADLINE> Large Quantities of Illegal VCDs Seized in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 1.89 million
pieces of illegal VCDs smuggled in various forms in south China's
Guangdong Province have been seized this year, according to local
customs sources.
</P>
<P>
The illegal VCDs were mainly smuggled in mixed with imported
materials, hidden in containers, or shipped in secretly.
</P>
<P>
Customs sources said this year there were eight cases each
involving over 10,000 pieces of CDs.
</P>
<P>
On January 16, customs officials in Shenzhen City captured two
smuggling vessels which carried more than 1.13 million VCDs, about
700,000 of which had pornographic contents.
</P>
<P>
Since the end of last year, customs in Guangdong have
intensified the crackdown on smuggling VCDs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
