<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment to Hebei Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 5.91 billion
U.S. dollars of foreign investment flowed into north China's Hebei
Province in the past five years, Provincial Governor Ye Liansong
said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 5,387 foreign-funded enterprises approved by the
province, 2,309 have started operation, Ye said at a provincial
meeting on using foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The average investment in each project has increased from
977,000 U.S. dollars in 1992 to last year's 1.66 million
U.S. dollars and the number of projects each involving 10 million
U.S. dollars has surpassed 400.
</P>
<P>
So far some top 500 companies in the world including Siemens,
Matsushita and Chai Tai have opened businesses in Hebei. Their
investment covers a wide range of subjects including
infrastructures, high-tech and pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment has also been used in technological
transformation of 300 state-owned enterprises and import of
equipment from abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
