<HEADLINE> Argentina Registers 11,000 Cases of AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, February 12 (Xinhua) -- About 11,500 HIV virus
carriers contracted AIDS in Argentina by the end of 1997, the
health ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A document, drafted by the National Program on War Against
Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), revealed that 100,000
persons infected with the HIV virus have been registered in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The study states that the increase in the number of declared
patients is primarily among groups of persons between the ages of
15-34.
</P>
<P>
The report said that AIDS is the second cause of death among
men between 20-34 years old, after deaths caused by accidents.
</P>
<P>
47 percent of the contagion during the 1996-1997 period was
through sexual contact, 43 percent through blood, 6.7 percent via
perinatal contagion, and the rest through unknown ways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
