<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Brisk in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange,
one of the two bourses in China, saw brisk A-share trading but
sluggish B-share trading in January.
</P>
<P>
The stock's composite Index closed at 1,222.90 points at the
end of January, up 2.41 percent over the previous month. The
turnover of A-shares reached 77.78 billion yuan in January, which
had only three trading weeks because of the Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
Affected by sluggish stock markets in Southeast Asia and
Hong Kong, the B-shares experienced a bearish market with
index falling by 7.76 points to close at 46.92 points, the lowest
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
A total of 785 million yuan of B-shares changed hands during the
month.
</P>
<P>
Last month also witnessed a brisk trading of treasury bonds,
with a total of 100 billion yuan changing hands.
</P>
<P>
The fund market recorded a turnover of 832 million yuan last
month, up nearly 107 percent over the previous month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
