<HEADLINE> Hungary Prepares to Join Military Action Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian Foreign Minister
Kovacs Laszlo said on Thursday that his country is willing to join
the possible international military actions against Iraq if a
political solution can not be found to the crisis arising out of
the United Nations weapons inspections in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here, Kovacs said the Hungarian
government will submit a draft resolution regarding its decision
to parliament next week.
</P>
<P>
He explained that Hungary's participation in the military
action means that it will allow the use of its air space and
military airports, and in the event of casualties, it will send
medical teams to concerned regions.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister clarified that Hungary's willingness to
take part in potential military action against Iraq has nothing to
do with its entry into the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO). 
</P>
