<HEADLINE> Coins Dug Up From Park Spring In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 40 kg of coins have
been removed from a spring in the town of Dali in south China's
Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
They were thrown by tourists into the spring in Butterfly
Spring Park, a popular tourist resort. The coins were removed by
park employees while cleaning the spring.
</P>
<P>
Most are five-fen, two-fen, and one-fen coins, and there are
various commemorative and old coins.
</P>
<P>
There is a block of stone in the middle of the spring with a
cleft and many tourists try to throw coins into it with the idea
that it will bring them good luck, according to park keepers.
</P>
<P>
Other tourists just toss coins into the spring and enjoy
watching them drift slowly down.
</P>
<P>
In April and May, thousands of butterflies can be seen in the
trees around the spring and skimming its surface.
</P>
