<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas-Backed Businesses Becoming Shanghai's Key Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-financed businesses
have become Shanghai's major exporters as more and more overseas
investors are putting their investment into production projects.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Shanghai Municipal Committee of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation disclosed that Shanghai earned
14.724 billion U.S. dollars from exports last year, a rise of
11.22 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
And 5.2 billion U.S. dollars were made by overseas-financed
enterprises. Specialized foreign trade companies made 4.3 billion
U.S. dollars in earnings from exports in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-financed businesses contributed 80 percent to the
city's export increase in 1997. Their exports stood at only one
billion U.S. dollars five years ago, accounting for 15 percent of
the city's total exports of the time.
</P>
<P>
Local foreign trade officials attributed the export increase by
overseas-financed ventures to the rapid growth of such businesses,
and to a fair product mix and an advantageous marketing network
overseas.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai approved the establishment of 1,802 overseas-financed
projects last year, of which 994 are industrial projects involving
a contractual use of 3.043 billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds,
accounting for 57.19 percent of the city's total investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the municipality had altogether
approved the establishment of 17,500 overseas-financed businesses
which had employed 948,000 workers.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to further improve services for overseas-backed
enterprises in operation, and continue to offer export-oriented
overseas-backed businesses preferential treatment in taxation in a
bid to encourage them to export more.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the city plans to attract more overseas-backed
enterprises to the Waigaoqiao Free Trade Zone in Pudong and boost
the zone's storage and trading functions by way of developing the
processing trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
