<HEADLINE> Chinese Providing TV Programs In Ethnic Minority Language </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, February 13 (Xinhua) -- The 300 million Mongolians in
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region can now watch "Water
Margins", the TV program based on a classic novel -- in Mongolian.
</P>
<P>
The 43-part series was being shown on Chinese television during
the Spring Festival (Chinese Lunar New Year) at the end of
January. To help the ethnic minority people follow the story
better, the regional TV station dubbed the original Chinese
version using Mongolian.
</P>
<P>
The series was based on the novel of the same name, which is
one of the four most famous Chinese literary classics, about a
well-known farmer uprising during the Song Dynasty (960-1279).
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, serializations of the other three classic
novels, "Romance of the Three Kingdoms", "Dream of Red Mansions",
and "Pilgrimage to the West", have been quite popular with Chinese
television audiences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
