<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Book on Great Changes in China Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- A Book depicting the great
changes during the period when China first introduced the policies
of reform and opening up in 1978 has been published by the
Guangzhou Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The book, entitled "1978: Great Turn for China", has 13
chapters with over 500,000 Chinese characters.
</P>
<P>
The book reveals actual historical events taking place during
the period between October of 1976 to December of 1978, including
the cracking down on the "Gang of Four", and the Third Plenary
Session of the 11th Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The book also has descriptions of the Deng Xiaoping Theory and
its deep influence on China's economic development and other
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Author of the book Ye Yonglie, a writer from Shanghai Writers'
Association, is famous for writing scientific novels and
biographies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
