<HEADLINE> Angola Draws Namibia 3-3 in African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Angola overcame a two-goal
deficit to draw Namibia 3-3 in their African Cup of Nations soccer
match in Bobo Dioulasso, Burkina Faso, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Twenty minutes into action, Namibia's Nauseb tipped a pass from
Auseb Mohammed to Gervatius Yuri-Khob, who beat an offside trap to
score the opening goal.
</P>
<P>
Nauseb made the score 2-0 several minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Angola reduced the deficit one minute into the second half when
Lazaro DaCosta headed in a corner kick.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes later Yuri-Khob made it 3-1 but then Angola came
back and Fernando De Soussa scored on a penalty shot in the 67th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Angola leveled the score with a blast from Mohamed.
</P>
<P>
The result puts Angola in a tie with defending champions South
Africa for second place in Group C. Both teams have one game yet
to play in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
