<HEADLINE> Togo Gets First-ever Nations Cup Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Togo snatched its first-ever
African Nations Cup victory Thursday by beating Ghana 2-1 in
Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso.
</P>
<P>
In the 25th minute, Togo's German-based striker Bachirou Salou,
neatly laid on the chance for Franck Dote to beat Simon Addo from
10 meters range.
</P>
<P>
Sammy Johnson made it 1-1 when he converted a penalty kick
eight minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Togo, which hardly raised an attack in the second half, hit the
winner in the dying seconds as Mohamed Coubadja-Toure sprinted
past two Ghanaian defenders to find the target. 
</P>
</TEXT>
