<HEADLINE> Tunisia Takes First Victory in African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, Feburary 12 (Xinhua) -- World Cup qualifier Tunisia
took its first win in the 1998 African Nations Cup in Ouagadougou
in Burkina Faso on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 runner-up, which lost to Ghana 2-0 in their Group B
opening match, overcame Democratic Congo 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia took the lead in the 31st minute through Mahdi Slimane
after Faouzi Rouissi missed a 14th minute penalty.
</P>
<P>
Democratic Congo equalized in the 36th minute through Kimoto
Okitankoyi.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia grabbed the game in the 76th minute when substitute
Zied Tlemcani made it 2-1 after a counter-attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
