<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Will Concentrade on Three Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will put more
emphasis on the information, biochemical, and new materials
industries, Mayor Xu Kuangdi told the first session of the 11th
Municipal People's Congress yesterday.
</P>
<P>
These three industries will be economic pillars at the start of
the next century. Shanghai has started its information industry by
becoming an information hub and it will continue to focus on
software and computer services, and develop a new generation of
network computers and artificial intelligence.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's growing biochemical and pharmaceutical industries
will become more dependent on biotechnology, the mayor said. There
will be more investment in new pharmaceutical products,
agricultural chemicals, organic foods, and
environmentally-friendly drugs.
</P>
<P>
Xu stressed that hi-tech industries are the key to Shanghai's
economic growth. Research institutes are expected to work more
closely with businesses, and by the year 2000, the majority of
Shanghai's large enterprises should have their own product
research facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
