<HEADLINE> Hainan Island Development Zone Establishes Chemical Center (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The China Everbright Group by last year had purchased 20
percent of Kumagai-Gumi (HK) Ltd., a major land developer in
Yangpu, showing the support of Hong Kong businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The State Planning Commission approved construction of the
second phase at Yangpu Port and a glass project, which had an
investment of 777 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The State Council, China's highest administrative body, has
also approved a Singapore-financed pulp mill in the zone, which
will have an annual production capacity of 600,000 tons, and cost
10.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A number of other projects like a high-speed wire rod plant
costing 450 million yuan, and a rice processing factory costing
170 million yuan are being undertaken.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure in the development zone is also being
completed. An expressway linking Yangpu and Haikou is open, and
one from Yangpu to Sanya on the southern tip of the island is
being built.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of Yangpu Port will add three berths for ships
of 35,000 DWT and will allow it to handle 2.2 million tons of
cargo a year.
</P>
<P>
On December 8, 1997, representatives of the Provincial
Government, CNOOC, Kumagai-Gumi (HK), and the Special Economic
Zone Office of the State Council met in Beijing and agreed to give
preferential treatment to land, water, power, and gas to people
who invest in major industrial projects like chemical fertilizers
and pulp in the Yangpu Economic Development Zone. 
</P>
