<HEADLINE> Chirac Renews Call for Peaceful Solution to Iraqi Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac, on a visit to Austria Thursday, once again called for a
peaceful solution to the crisis over weapons inspections in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after talks with Austrian President
Thomas Klestil and Chancellor Viktor Klima, Chirac said that
France will do all it can to seek a diplomatic solution to the
iraqi crisis and to stop the U.S. from using force again Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed France's desire to avoid military action in the
crisis, saying women and children should not be needlessly killed.
</P>
<P>
"I do not question the need to oblige Saddam Hussein to respect
all the decisions of the (U.N.) Security Council," Chirac said, "I
simply mean that, if we can do so without sending bombs and
killing women and children, it would be better."
</P>
<P>
France, Russia and China have been opposed to the use of
military force in settling the Iraqi crisis while the United
States and Britain have repeatedly threatened to take military
action to solve the issue.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question on how long the international community
should give Iraq to comply with relevant U.N. resolutions, Chirac
said: "When it involves humanitarian issues, France's patience is
limitless."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the French president said Iraq must fulfil its
obligations by implementing relevant U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
"We want U.N. resolutions to be fully respected," he said,
"This means that Iraq must accept the obligations and inspections
of UNSCOM" (the U.N. Special Commission inspecting Iraqi weapons
sites). 
</P>
</TEXT>
