<HEADLINE> Overseas-Backed Businesses of East China's Zhejiang Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 13 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-backed businesses of
east China's Zhejiang Province have recorded good economic returns.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, 6,500 overseas-backed enterprises
in operation chalked up 101.78 billion yuan in sales volume,
netted 3.623 billion yuan of profits and earned 2.83 billion
U.S. dollars from exports in 1997, all showing marked increases
over the comparable figures of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Twenty of the province's overseas-backed enterprises are
included in a recently released list of China's top 500
overseas-financed enterprises for the period 1996-1997.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the province had altogether approved the
establishment of 14,619 overseas-financed enterprises by the end
of last year, with contracts involving the use of 17.97 billion
U.S. dollars of overseas investment. The actual paid-in overseas
funds was 7.04 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
While simplifying procedures for approving overseas-backed
enterprises and improving services, the province has also been
tightening supervision over the implementation of contracts for
overseas-financed enterprises over the past years.  
</P>
