<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures on Ruud Gullit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Following is factfile on Ruud
Gullit who was replaced as manager of English premier league
Chelsea on Thursday:
</P>
<P>
1962: Born in Amsterdam.
</P>
<P>
1978: Joined Dutch club Harlem.
</P>
<P>
1981: Made international debut for the Netherlands against
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
1982: Moved to Feyenoord.
</P>
<P>
1985: Transferred to PSV Eindhoven.
</P>
<P>
1987: Signed by AC Milan for world record 5.5 million pounds
(8.4 million U.S. dollars). Voted European and World Footballer of
the Year.
</P>
<P>
1988: Led Milan to Italian league title and captained
Netherlands to European soccer title.
</P>
<P>
1993: Won third Italian League winners' medal with Milan before
joining Sampdoria.
</P>
<P>
1994: Made international comeback against Scotland but walked
out of training camp after another argument with manager with the
World Cup less than three weeks away. In all, made 66 appearances
for the Netherlands, scoring 16 goals. Moved back to Milan for
seven months before returning to Sampdoria.
</P>
<P>
1995: Signed two-year contract with Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
1996: Named as Chelsea's player-manager.
</P>
<P>
1997: Led Chelsea to beat Middlesbrough 2-0 in F.A. Cup final.
</P>
<P>
1998: Replaced as manager of Chelsea by former Italian
international Gianluca Vialli.
</P>
</TEXT>
