<HEADLINE> Abede Pele Retires from Ghana National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Ghana's Abede Pele, veteran of
five African Nations Cups, said on Thursday he would retire from
the national team at the end of the current competition in Burkina
Faso.
</P>
<P>
Pele, 34, announced his decision in a statement ahead of
Ghana's Group B match against Togo in Ouagadougou.
</P>
<P>
"I regret to announce that I have decided to retire from the
national team, The Black Stars, with effect from the end of the
current African Cup of Nations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This decision is predicated on the premise that after 17 years
service to the national team, The Black Stars, the competing
demands of club and international football are inevitably exacting
their toll on my depleting stock of energy." 
</P>
