<HEADLINE> Albright:: US to Check Russia's Contract With Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright said Thursday that the United States would
check a report, published in the Washington Post, which alleged
Russia had negotiated to sell Iraq highly-sensitive dual-use
technology that could be used to produce biological weapons.
</P>
<P>
"We'll certainly follow it, as we see it as a very serious
issue," Albright told the House International Relations Committee.
</P>
