<HEADLINE> Large Quantities of Drugs Burned in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Greece set large quantities of
drugs on fire Thursday to show its determination to combat the
growing drug problem in the country.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, 43 kilograms of heroin, 23 kilograms of cocaine and
one ton of Indian cannabis, were incinerated in Elefsina, near
Athens. 
</P>
