<HEADLINE> Canada's Bombardier Gets U.S. Aircraft Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian aerospace giant
Bombardier Inc. announced Thursday that it had received a firm 1.4
billion U.S. dollar order from American Eagle.
</P>
<P>
American Eagle, the regional airline affiliate of American
Airlines, has now finalized its order for 25 firm and 25 optioned
70-seat Canadian Regional Jet Series 700 aircraft, Bombardier said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The deal, originally announced at the Paris Air Show last year,
was subject to completion of definitive aircraft purchase and
financing agreements, it added.
</P>
<P>
Delivery of the jets are scheduled to begin in early 2001.
</P>
<P>
The Montreal-based corporation had revenues of about 5.5
billion Canadian dollars last year and employs 46,000 people in
Canada and other countries. 
</P>
